<div dir="ltr">The failure below (from OpenBSD5-amd64) shows unresolved calls to pthread &quot;setpshared&quot; interfaces for mutex and condition vars.   Thesw were not part of the initial POSIX threads specification, and therefore configure-time check is required before these calls can safely be included.<div>
<br></div><div>Like my previous report (unresolved __sync_synchronize) this is from the osc/sm component code, and there is no relation to VT (it just happens that otfmerge-mpi is the first executable linked to libmpi).<br>
